The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for automatic portrait matting on mobile devices. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of multi-branch dilated convolution with linear bottleneck blocks, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also deals with real-time inference, which is related to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes a new model that outperforms the state-of-the-art while being faster and having fewer parameters, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
